Reasoning: The paper deals with decision-making and game scenarios in multi-agent settings, which are typical topics in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new structure of preference-sight trees, which can be seen as a type of logical structure (cs.LO). The paper discusses the relation between different solution concepts and explores whether larger sight always contributes to better outcomes, which are topics in mechanism design (cs.MA) and decision theory (cs.DS).
